  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "An oil painting on panel by **Henriëtte Ronner-Knip** (Amsterdam, 1821 – Brussels, 1909), depicting a cat and four kittens on a piano — one of the signature themes of this enormously successful 19th-century Dutch-Belgian painter. Acquired by Teylers Museum in **2012** with support from the VriendenLoterij, the work is designated one of the museum's **50 Topstukken**. A kitten from the painting, \"Brammetje,\" has become a mascot for Teylers' children's educational programmes.",
